No. 55/1/1/CF-70
GOVERNMENT OF INDIA
CABINET SECRETARIAT
(Departmene of Cabinet Affairs)
MOST IMMEDIATE
New Delhi, the 30th June 1970.
9th Asadha 1892.
The undersigned is directed to state that with effect from
the afternoon of June 30, 1970,
(i) Shri On Mehta assumed the office of Minister of
State in the Department of Parliamentary Affairss
(ii) Shri AK, Kisku assumed the office of Deputy Minister
in the Ministry of Education & Youth Services;
(iii) Shri Raghbir Singh Panjhazari assumed the office of
Deputy Minister in the Department of Parliamentary
Affairs;
(iv) Shri P. Parthas arathy assumed the office of Deputy
Minister in the Department of Parliamentary Affairs; and
(v) Shri Bishwa Nath Roy assumed the office of Deputy
Minister in the Ministry of Labour, Bmployment and
Rehabilitation.
(R.N. Kalia)
for Cabinet Secretary.
To
All Members of the Council of Ministers.
Copy forwarded to the Secretary to the Prime Minister/the
Joint Secretary to the Prime Minister/the Private Secretary to
the Prime Minister, for information.
Copy forwarded to the Secretary to the President/the
Secretary to the Vice-President, for information..
Rmaha
(R.N. Kalia)
Under Secretary to the Cabinet.
.......2/-

Copy forwarded to all Secretaries/Special Secretaries/
Additional Secretaries to the Government of India/Chaiman,
Relway Board/Secretary, Election Commission/Secretary, Union
Public Service Commission/Comptroller and Auditor General of
India, for information.
Copy forwarded to all Minis trics/Departments of the
Government of India/Lok Sabha Secretariat/Rajya Sabha Secretariat/
Establishment Officer, Ministry of Home Affairs, for information.
Hhahia
(R.N. Kalia)
Under Secretary to the Cabinet.
KATARIA*
250 copies.
